            <title><![CDATA[Pointers For Marvel Rivals And Path of Exile 2, What To Play Before AC Shadows Arrives, And More Of The Week's Top Tips]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-solo-tips-ff7-rebirth-steam-deck-1851758135</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/pointers-for-marvel-rivals-and-path-of-exile-2-what-to-play-before-ac-shadows-arrives-and-more-of-the-weeks-top-tips.1104363/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-solo-tips-ff7-rebirth-steam-deck-1851758135<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="5ec33c55fc03140bb15e9d5de6de1035" data-recommend-id="image://5ec33c55fc03140bb15e9d5de6de1035" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft<!-- -->, <!-- -->Square Enix / Valve / Claire Jackson / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sunblink<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Chibig / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5ec33c55fc03140bb15e9d5de6de1035" data-recommend-id="image://5ec33c55fc03140bb15e9d5de6de1035" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Whether you want to tackle <em>Path of Exile 2 </em>solo, make the most of Mr. Fantastic’s stretchy powers in <em>Marvel Rivals</em>, or just get <em>Final Fantasy VII Rebirth </em>looking and running its best on your Steam Deck, we’ve got the tips for you.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4aaa66cbec224d471075aa5bb76bf2bd" data-recommend-id="image://4aaa66cbec224d471075aa5bb76bf2bd" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A character holds up a fist to a gloomy sky in promotional art for Path of Exile 2." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A character holds up a fist to a gloomy sky in promotional art for Path of Exile 2." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4aaa66cbec224d471075aa5bb76bf2bd" data-recommend-id="image://4aaa66cbec224d471075aa5bb76bf2bd" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A character holds up a fist to a gloomy sky in promotional art for Path of Exile 2." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Many will argue that the best solo class in <em>Path of Exile 2</em> isn’t the one topping the meta currently but the one you enjoy the most. That’s true…<em>to some extent</em>. Some builds prove viable from the get-go, capable of pushing all of the end-game content across Wraeclast. Others, not so much. For example, the Warrior, while entertaining as you smash your foes with reckless abandon, poses a problem in the end-game because most late-game enemies and bosses excel against melee builds. But seeing as you can only choose one, we recommend starting with a minion build, which means <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-witch-class-skills-passive-unearth-1851736773&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-witch-class-skills-passive-unearth-1851736773">selecting the Witch</a></span>! - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/path-exile-2-solo-play-best-class-witch-mercenary-1851755253&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/path-exile-2-solo-play-best-class-witch-mercenary-1851755253">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6185e14fd9d9033c0f29e1c4769ff739" data-recommend-id="image://6185e14fd9d9033c0f29e1c4769ff739" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows the main character, Naoe, in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows the main character, Naoe, in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6185e14fd9d9033c0f29e1c4769ff739" data-recommend-id="image://6185e14fd9d9033c0f29e1c4769ff739" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows the main character, Naoe, in Assassin’s Creed Shadows." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p> Following <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-assassins-creed-shadows-delay-march-february-1851736266&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-assassins-creed-shadows-delay-march-february-1851736266">multiple delays</a></span> that have pushed the game deeper into 2025, along with reports of this being the biggest <em>AC</em> game with the longest development time in the franchise, <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em> is nearly upon us. Of course, there’s still time to complete a game or two beforehand. While February is positively <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/february-2025-video-game-releases-monster-hunter-avowed-1851713876&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/february-2025-video-game-releases-monster-hunter-avowed-1851713876">jam-packed with new game releases</a></span>, you may want to hit up your backlog instead of paying cash for something new before <em>Shadows</em> (or scope out some possible deals on older games). Here are a few titles we recommend you stomp through first!  - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-games-like-open-world-rpg-ninja-1851755223&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/assassins-creed-shadows-games-like-open-world-rpg-ninja-1851755223">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="5c5d4a5eb8195c546b3b0ae56d142d53" data-recommend-id="image://5c5d4a5eb8195c546b3b0ae56d142d53" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Red XIII looks to the side during a cutscene in FF7 Rebirth runing on a Steam Deck." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Red XIII looks to the side during a cutscene in FF7 Rebirth runing on a Steam Deck." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix / Valve / Claire Jackson / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5c5d4a5eb8195c546b3b0ae56d142d53" data-recommend-id="image://5c5d4a5eb8195c546b3b0ae56d142d53" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Red XIII looks to the side during a cutscene in FF7 Rebirth runing on a Steam Deck." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Let’s cut to the chase; <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-steam-deck-verified-performance-1851748592&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-steam-deck-verified-performance-1851748592">it’s a small miracle that <em>Final Fantasy VII Rebirth </em>runs on the Steam Deck</a></span>. This is a game so visually demanding that it’s the poster child for <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ps5-pro-playstation-unboxing-inside-review-comparison-1851688605&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ps5-pro-playstation-unboxing-inside-review-comparison-1851688605">the $800 PS5 Pro</a></span>. Yet, the power of Valve’s handheld device is roughly comparable to last gen’s PS4. On top of that, even Square Enix games that <em>can </em>run on last-generation hardware <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/visions-of-mana-steam-deck-performance-settings-1851636872&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/visions-of-mana-steam-deck-performance-settings-1851636872">have struggled on the Steam Deck</a></span>. So you can probably understand that my expectations for <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-review-ps5-1851276129&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-review-ps5-1851276129"><em>Final Fantasy VII Rebirth</em></a></span><em> </em>were pretty low. If Cloud’s adventure ran well enough that I could sneak in some games of Queen’s Blood on the go, I’d consider it a win. - Timothy Monbleau <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ff7-rebirth-best-steam-deck-graphics-settings-1851754163&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ff7-rebirth-best-steam-deck-graphics-settings-1851754163">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2c5b806f86f30d8d835055c133fac8b2" data-recommend-id="image://2c5b806f86f30d8d835055c133fac8b2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller monkey race forward while a blurred image of gameplay decorates the background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller monkey race forward while a blurred image of gameplay decorates the background." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2c5b806f86f30d8d835055c133fac8b2" data-recommend-id="image://2c5b806f86f30d8d835055c133fac8b2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller monkey race forward while a blurred image of gameplay decorates the background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Donkey Kong Country Returns HD</em> marks the second time the popular Wii game has been ported to another Nintendo console. But it’s the first time it’s been given the full high-definition treatment. The game certainly looks better than ever, though it’s worth noting there are no meaningful changes to the gameplay added in this version.  - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-country-returns-hd-switch-how-long-1851754095&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-country-returns-hd-switch-how-long-1851754095">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f4016b6a177d201de48a59cfa07b8553" data-recommend-id="image://f4016b6a177d201de48a59cfa07b8553" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A promotional screenshot of Path of Exile 2. The Monk character is attacking several monsters with a staff while a large bipedal creature prepares to swing its club." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A promotional screenshot of Path of Exile 2. The Monk character is attacking several monsters with a staff while a large bipedal creature prepares to swing its club." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Grinding Gear Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f4016b6a177d201de48a59cfa07b8553" data-recommend-id="image://f4016b6a177d201de48a59cfa07b8553" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A promotional screenshot of Path of Exile 2. The Monk character is attacking several monsters with a staff while a large bipedal creature prepares to swing its club." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>ARPGs like <em>Path of Exile 2</em> and portable gaming devices like the Steam Deck go together like spaghetti and meatballs. Fighting huge mobs of enemies and grinding out rare loot is perfect for pick-up-and-play gaming, especially while you lay in bed listening to all those podcasts your friends keep bugging you to check out. Granted, this is only a great experience if the game you’re playing runs well on Valve’s flagship portable device, so how does <em>Path of Exile 2</em> hold up? - Timothy Monbleau <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-steam-deck-graphics-settings-diablo-1851754197&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/path-of-exile-2-steam-deck-graphics-settings-diablo-1851754197">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="791602b12f5168c3c92b5d69b6d0b78c" data-recommend-id="image://791602b12f5168c3c92b5d69b6d0b78c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Captain America stands with his shield against a fantasy background with a large building." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Captain America stands with his shield against a fantasy background with a large building." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="791602b12f5168c3c92b5d69b6d0b78c" data-recommend-id="image://791602b12f5168c3c92b5d69b6d0b78c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Captain America stands with his shield against a fantasy background with a large building." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>It is only fitting that the First Avenger himself, Captain America, was one of the first heroes to join <em>Marvel Rivals</em>. For a character whose primary weapon is a shield, it makes sense that Cap would take on <em>Rivals’</em> version of the Tank role as a Vanguard. However, unlike beefier Tanks, the Sentinel of Liberty requires a little more finesse than other characters like Hulk.  - Simon Estey <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-how-to-play-captain-america-tank-1851754920&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-how-to-play-captain-america-tank-1851754920">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1bf1a93992c98830574afb53b3c9d7b3" data-recommend-id="image://1bf1a93992c98830574afb53b3c9d7b3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mr. Fantastic stands in a hangar." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mr. Fantastic stands in a hangar." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1bf1a93992c98830574afb53b3c9d7b3" data-recommend-id="image://1bf1a93992c98830574afb53b3c9d7b3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mr. Fantastic stands in a hangar." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>While he is a little late to <em>Marvel Rivals,</em> the namesake of Marvel’s first family has joined the multiplayer hero shooter. Despite taking on the role of a Duelist, <em>Rivals’ </em>version of DPS, the character also contains elements of the Vanguard Class, making him an elastic and versatile choice.  - Simon Estey <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-mr-fantastic-elasticity-gauge-how-to-play-1851755270&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-mr-fantastic-elasticity-gauge-how-to-play-1851755270">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7e2d74b5c2213db9a840d545c8291a65" data-recommend-id="image://7e2d74b5c2213db9a840d545c8291a65" data-format="jpg" data-width="1492" data-height="838" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A cute dog, rabbit, bird, and the Hello Kitty character stand on a bridge in a peaceful-looking forest." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A cute dog, rabbit, bird, and the Hello Kitty character stand on a bridge in a peaceful-looking forest." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sunblink</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7e2d74b5c2213db9a840d545c8291a65" data-recommend-id="image://7e2d74b5c2213db9a840d545c8291a65" data-format="jpg" data-width="1492" data-height="838" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A cute dog, rabbit, bird, and the Hello Kitty character stand on a bridge in a peaceful-looking forest." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Now that <em>Hello Kitty Island Adventure</em> is available on Nintendo Switch and PC, you may be curious if you can play with your friends on other platforms, or perhaps if you can carry your save over to a new platform. We’ll fill you in on everything you need to know about the game’s crossplay and cross-save functionality below. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/hello-kitty-island-adventure-crossplay-cross-save-1851755126&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/hello-kitty-island-adventure-crossplay-cross-save-1851755126">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="764904bed0176058271af3a064324ffc" data-recommend-id="image://764904bed0176058271af3a064324ffc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1079" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mika the witch stands in front of a large mysterious statue in the background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mika the witch stands in front of a large mysterious statue in the background." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Chibig / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="764904bed0176058271af3a064324ffc" data-recommend-id="image://764904bed0176058271af3a064324ffc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1079" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mika the witch stands in front of a large mysterious statue in the background." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Cozy, laid-back games have a tendency to feature a bit of character customization, and <em>Mika and the Witch’s Mountain</em> is no different. In this relaxing, delivery-focused game, you can equip the titular character with a variety of outfits and charms that give her a bit of additional personality. While a few of these can be earned during the story, most will have to be purchased from a somewhat hidden location. Here’s where to find it. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mika-witchs-mountain-new-outfits-charms-mountain-gusts-1851755188&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mika-witchs-mountain-new-outfits-charms-mountain-gusts-1851755188">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2d5cf4626c55caf625a5b9be08b71ac4" data-recommend-id="image://2d5cf4626c55caf625a5b9be08b71ac4" data-format="jpg" data-width="2395" data-height="1343" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller ape in a baseball cap stand in a jungle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller ape in a baseball cap stand in a jungle." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2d5cf4626c55caf625a5b9be08b71ac4" data-recommend-id="image://2d5cf4626c55caf625a5b9be08b71ac4" data-format="jpg" data-width="2395" data-height="1343" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Donkey Kong and a smaller ape in a baseball cap stand in a jungle." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Donkey Kong Country Returns HD</em> is the second re-release of the original Wii version of this classic platformer. Prettier graphics aside, basically everything fans love (or hate) about this <em>Kong </em>outing remains intact to enjoy all over again—or for the first time. If you’re new to the game, we’ve got three tips that we think might help you in the early hoursAnd if you’re really struggling, the second tip might be especially helpful, so read on! - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-country-returns-hd-banana-coins-map-keys-1851754198&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/donkey-kong-country-returns-hd-banana-coins-map-keys-1851754198">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
